column2: #load spatial data
#### DOWNLOAD AT CENSUS TRACT LEVEL
stl_cnty <- tracts(state = "MO", county = 510, cb = FALSE)
Using FIPS code '29' for state 'MO'
stl <- tracts(state = "MO", county = 189, cb = FALSE)
Using FIPS code '29' for state 'MO'
stclr <- tracts(state = "IL", county = 163, cb = FALSE)
Using FIPS code '17' for state 'IL'
madison <- tracts(state = "IL", county = 119, cb = FALSE)
Using FIPS code '17' for state 'IL'
#convert to sf object
stl_cnty <- st_as_sf(stl_cnty)
stl <- st_as_sf(stl)
stclr <- st_as_sf(stclr)
madison <- st_as_sf(madison)
#clean data
stl_cnty <- stl_cnty %>%
select( GEOID, geometry) %>%
transform( GEOID = as.numeric(GEOID))
stl <- stl %>%
select( GEOID, geometry) %>%
transform( GEOID = as.numeric(GEOID))
stclr <- stclr %>%
select( GEOID, geometry) %>%
transform( GEOID = as.numeric(GEOID))
madison <- madison %>%
select( GEOID, geometry) %>%
transform( GEOID = as.numeric(GEOID))
#write shapefiles
st_write(stl_cnty, here("data", "shapefiles", "stl_county.shp"),
delete_dsn = TRUE)
